documentType: aircraft registration and bill of sale records
summary: This document is a collection of FAA aircraft registration and bill of sale records for a Sikorsky S-76C helicopter (serial 760750, tail numbers N750A, N722JE, and N162AE). It traces the ownership from manufacturer Keystone Helicopter Corporation to Air Ghislaine Inc., then to ASI Wings LLC, and finally a sale in 2019. The records include registration applications, bills of sale, and correspondence regarding special number assignments.

connections.description: Clark signed as Senior VP/Controller for Aetna Inc., the managing member of ASI Wings LLC, on a bill of sale.
Westbrook signed documents as Managing Member of ASI Wings LLC and as Assistant Corporate Secretary of Aetna Inc., its managing member.
Sterling, a legal assistant at DeBee Gilchrist, wrote a letter on behalf of ASI Wings LLC to the FAA.

events.title: Sale from Keystone to Sikorsky
events.description: Keystone Helicopter Corporation sells the S-76C helicopter (serial 760750, N750A) to Sikorsky Aircraft Corporation.

events.title: Sale from Sikorsky to Air Ghislaine
events.description: Sikorsky Aircraft Corporation sells the same helicopter to Air Ghislaine Inc.

events.title: Special Number Assignment N722JE
events.description: FAA issues an Assignment of Special Registration Numbers (AC Form 8050-64) authorizing a change from N750A to N722JE for Air Ghislaine Inc.

events.title: Sale to ASI Wings LLC
events.description: Freedom Air International, Inc. sells the helicopter (N722JE) to ASI Wings LLC via a Warranty Bill of Sale.

events.title: Special Number Assignment N162AE
events.description: FAA issues an Assignment of Special Registration Numbers authorizing a change from N722JE to N162AE for ASI Wings LLC. The authorization later expires unused.

events.title: Sale from ASI Wings LLC
events.description: ASI Wings LLC sells the helicopter (N722JE) to an unnamed purchaser via an Aircraft Bill of Sale.

keyFacts: The helicopter (Sikorsky S-76C, serial 760750) was originally manufactured by Keystone Helicopter Corporation and carried tail number N750A.
Ownership transferred from Keystone to Sikorsky Aircraft Corp. (2008), then to Air Ghislaine Inc. (2008), then to ASI Wings LLC (2011), and was sold again in 2019.
ASI Wings LLC, the entity that owned the helicopter from 2011 to 2019, is managed by Aetna Inc., as indicated by signatories.
There were attempts to change the tail number from N722JE to N162AE in 2011, but the authorization expired in 2012 without the change being completed.

The documents show a pattern of corporate ownership and detailed FAA registration procedures, with no direct mention of Jeffrey Epstein, victims, or illegal activity within this specific set of forms.
